      "left": [
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "value": "For symmetric frequency distributions, the drifting branch contributes no net order parameter after averaging, so the derivation keeps only the locked branch."
        },
        {
          "kind": "math",
          "latex": "g(\\omega)=g(-\\omega)",
          "displayMode": true
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "value": "This is the standard centered case: after shifting into the rotating frame, positive and negative detunings are balanced, so the drifting oscillators do not produce a net contribution to the order parameter."
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "value": "That leaves the delta-supported term from Eq. 10."
        },
        {
          "kind": "text",
          "value": "If the centered distribution is asymmetric, that cancellation is not exact, and Eq. 11 is no longer the correct reduced form by itself."
        }
      ],
